quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,All that exists on the earth will perish
  55,27,but the Face of your Lord will remain full of Majesty and Glory
  55,28,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s glories will both of you deny"
  55,29,"All who dwell in the heavens and the earth, implore Him for their needs, every moment He is busy in some mighty task"
  55,30,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s honors will both of you deny"
  55,31,"O you, the two burdens (jinns and mankind)! Soon We shall find the time to call you to account"
  55,32,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,33,"O you, the assembly of jinns and men! If you have the power to get away from the boundaries of the heavens and the earth (to escape from His punishment), then get away! You cannot get away except with Our Own authority"
  55,34,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s authorities will both of you deny"
  55,35,"The flames of fire and molten brass will be unleashed on you both, jinn and men, and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,37,When the heaven will burst and will become red like red hide
  55,38,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,39,On that Day neither man nor jinn will need be asked about his sins
  55,40,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,41,Because the sinners will be recognized by their faces and they shall be seized by their forelocks and their feet
  55,42,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,43,"It will be said to them: \"This is the hell which the culprits denied"
  55,44,They shall wander to and fro between fire and hot boiling water
  55,45,"Then, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s warnings will both of you deny"